# {{context|obsolete|transitive|lang=en}} To [[enclose]]; to take in; to [[harvest]].
#* Shakespeare
#*: He that ears my land spares my team and gives me leave to '''in''' the crop.

===Etymology 2===
{{etyl|ang|en}} ''[[inne]]''

====Adverb====
{{en-adv|-}}

# {{context|not comparable|lang=en}} Located [[indoors]], especially: at home or the office .<!--is this adjective?-->
#: ''Is Mr. Smith '''in'''?''
# [[move|Moving]] to the [[interior]] of a defined space, such as a building or room.
#: ''Suddenly a strange man walked '''in'''.''
# {{context|sports|lang=en}} Still [[eligible]] to [[play]], e.g. able to bat in cricket and baseball.
#: ''He went for the wild toss but wasn't able to stay '''in'''.''
# {{context|UK|lang=en}} abbreviation of [[in aid of]].
#: ''What's that '''in'''?''
# After the beginning of something.
